{"nodes": [{"id": "_knowledge_k09_sender_name_thailand", "label": "K09 Sender Name / Sender ID Thailand", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "_knowledge/K09-Sender-Name-Thailand.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "_knowledge_k09_sender_name_thailand_sender_name", "label": "Sender Name / Sender ID", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "_knowledge/K09-Sender-Name-Thailand.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Alphanumeric 'from' name (3-11 chars, A-Z/0-9, no Thai script, no generic words like BANK) registered separately with each operator (7-14 day approval, ~THB 1,000-5,000/sender/operator/yr). It is a brand asset: recognizable brand sender -> 98%+ open, unknown sender -> 60%, foreign number -> 15%. Unregistered sender = the #1 cause of hard-blocked (REJECTD) campaigns in Thailand."}, {"id": "_knowledge_k09_sender_name_thailand_multi_sender_strategy", "label": "Multi-Sender (Dedicated Sender ID) Strategy", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "_knowledge/K09-Sender-Name-Thailand.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "EasySlip/Thunder Solution register separate senders per use case (EasySlip = transactional, EasySlip-OTP/Thunder-AI = OTP, BANKTECH = banking-related alerts, BoostSMS = internal notifications). Why: trust is per use case, marketing throttling/complaints must not take OTP down with them, and compliance is easier. Trade-off: extra registration cost per sender."}], "edges": [{"source": "_knowledge_k09_sender_name_thailand", "target": "_knowledge_k08_thai_sms_market_nbtc", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "_knowledge/K09-Sender-Name-Thailand.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "_knowledge_k09_sender_name_thailand", "target"